{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17646058","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17646058"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:25:10+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:25:10+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18153"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18153","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18153"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10867"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78409"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10867","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10867"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18153"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63771"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25279"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25281"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26873"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78409","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78409"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe anatomical snuffbox is a triangular depression located on the lateral aspect of the wrist. It is bordered by tendons that are important landmarks in the musculoskeletal system. It has several boundaries.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following tendons forms the posterior boundary?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Abductor pollicis longus","Extensor pollicis brevis","Extensor pollicis longus","Flexor carpi radialis","Extensor carpi ulnaris"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eextensor pollicis longus\u003C/strong\u003E tendon forms the posterior boundary of the anatomical snuffbox. This tendon crosses over the tendons of the abductor pollicis longus and extensor pollicis brevis, which form the anterior boundary.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbductor pollicis longus\u003C/strong\u003E - This tendon forms part of the anterior boundary\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtensor pollicis brevis\u003C/strong\u003E - This tendon also forms part of the anterior boundary\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlexor carpi radialis\u003C/strong\u003E - This tendon is not involved in forming the boundaries of the anatomical snuffbox\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtensor carpi ulnaris\u003C/strong\u003E - This tendon is located on the ulnar side of the wrist and does not contribute to the anatomical snuffbox\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The anatomical snuffbox is a triangular depression on the lateral aspect of the wrist.","The extensor pollicis longus tendon forms the posterior boundary of the anatomical snuffbox.","The extensor pollicis brevis and abductor pollicis longus tendons form the anterior boundary of the anatomical snuffbox."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Raszewski JA, Black AC, Launico MV, et al. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Hand Compartments. [Updated 2023 Oct 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/books/NBK532942/","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences250"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63771"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18153"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63771","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63771"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-10T17:08:38+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-10T17:09:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10867"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78409"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving informat